The paper deals with distributed network computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus of the paper is on subgraph detection, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the running time of algorithms, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The algorithms are designed for networks, which is related to Network Architecture and Protocols (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the results for distributed property testing, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
